President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of Iowa due to flooding that occurred in May 2011. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected area. The funding will be available for debris removal, emergency protective measures, and hazard mitigation measures. Michael R. Scott has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the area. Additional designations may be made in the future if requested by the state and warranted by further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.